<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND COOLER - OIL FILTER
        AND HEADER - INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install water outlet tube in front cover. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050926">9.26</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>INSTALL OIL COOLER ASSEMBLY USING A NEW SQUARE CUT O-RING AT FRONT HEADER AND GASKET AT REAR
                        FILTER COOLER HEADER.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1050925" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3041" filename="../figeg3/EG3041.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.25.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Cooler Filter Header</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. OIl Cooler Bundle</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Cooler Front Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050926" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2476" filename="../figeg2/EG2476.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.26.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Water Outlet Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Front Cover</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a new O-Ring, install the filter header/oil cooler assembly to the crankcase. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050927">9.27</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                and
                <emph type="bold">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050928">9.28</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . Tighten to the special torque value. (See
                <emph type="bold">Appendix</emph>.)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bracket to retain water inlet tube to crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect the turbocharger oil inlet tube to the oil filter header elbow. Use a new sealing
                ring at the oil inlet tube nut.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050927" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg2465" filename="../figeg2/EG2465.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.27.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Lube Filter/Oil Cooler Header</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Water Inlet and Outlet O-Rings</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Cooler</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Water Outlet Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050928" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1727" filename="../figeg1/EG1727.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.28.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Water Inlet Tube Bracket/Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Water Inlet Tube</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Oil Cooler Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Oil Cooler</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. Oil Filter Header Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. Oil Filter Header Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. Lube Filter/Oil Cooler Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new oil filter as follows: Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050929">9.29</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new filter gasket with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Hand tighten filter 1-1/4 to 1-3/4 turns after gasket first contacts filter header.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>DO NOT OVERTIGHTEN FILTER. Damaged filter may fracture or leak.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prime lubricating system as described in Section 7,
                <emph type="bold">"Crankshaft, Main Bearings, Flywheel and Crankcase."</emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050929" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1725" filename="../figeg1/EG1725.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.29.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Filter</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Filter Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
